  "body":"Requirements:\r\n\r\n- [ ] A transport layer, probably websockets. [Sente](https://github.com/ptaoussanis/sente) appears to be the most popular WS library.\r\n- [ ] A service layer. Sente supports [http-kit](https://github.com/http-kit/http-kit), [Immutant v2+](http://immutant.org/), [nginx-clojure](https://github.com/nginx-clojure/nginx-clojure), node.js, [Aleph](https://github.com/ztellman/aleph).\r\n- [ ] A router: `reitit` is already being used on the front-end, and is [Purely Functional's Top Choice](https://purelyfunctional.tv/mini-guide/clojure-routers/).\r\n- [ ] A persistence layer: probably going with local Datomic, which runs on-top of a storage service like [PostgresQL](https://docs.datomic.com/on-prem/storage.html#sql-database), so that we can have the same data model on the backend (Datomic) and frontend (Datascript), which are datoms.\r\n- [ ] Assuming Datomic, we need to write synchronization logic or use a library such as [datsync](https://github.com/metasoarous/datsync).\r\n\r\nNote: these libraries/requirements are more of a suggestion and starting point than a final decision. These requirements can and may very well evolve or change.",
